title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a plan that outputs all creditors that do not have "SLETTET" in their name, and that have an id between 193000 and 194000. Output in textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log: Create a plan that retrieves all creditors whose names do not contain the substring "SLETTET" and whose id is between 193000 and 194000 (inclusive). Output the results to a plain text file.

log.thoughts: Query will filter creditor_id between 193000 and 194000 and exclude names containing 'SLETTET'.

steps.detailed_description: Load the creditor table with all columns (creditor_id, name, creditor_type) as the input dataset.

Filter the creditors to keep rows where creditor_id is between 193000 and 194000 (inclusive) and where name does NOT contain the substring 'SLETTET'. Input: full creditor dataset. Output: filtered creditors dataset.
Write the filtered creditors to a plain text file output.

log.thoughts: A straightforward extract-filter-output flow: load the creditor table, apply the id range and name exclusion, then persist to text.

title: Class: StepHandler created step dependencies and queue

operations.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name, creditor_type FROM creditor) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; id >= 193000 && id <= 194000 && !name.contains("SLETTET") }

log.thoughts: Created a two-operator subplan: read the creditor table, then filter by id range and exclude names containing SLETTET.

title: Class: StepHandler merged subplans to full plan

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; id >= 193000 && id <= 194000 && !name.contains("SLETTET") }

operations.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name, creditor_type FROM creditor) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; id >= 193000 && id <= 194000 && !name.contains("SLETTET")}

log.thoughts: Refined the plan to include a final textFileOutput operator so the filtered creditors are written to a plain text file. Ensured the input pulls creditor_id, name, and creditor_type from the creditor table, applies the requested filter for id range and substring exclusion, and outputs to a file. The plan remains a minimal DAG with correct operator arities and a valid data flow.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped the refined plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT creditor_id, name, creditor_type FROM (SELECT creditor_id, name, creditor_type FROM creditor) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val id = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val name = r.getField(1).toString; id >= 193000 && id <= 194000 && !name.contains("SLETTET")}
